############################################################
SCOUT WORD-FORMATTING & TYPOGRAPHY LAYER
(MS Word Copy-Paste Compliant)
Version: 1.0
Immutable Core
############################################################

All produced book text must use strict Markdown typography standards to ensure seamless formatting translation when copied and pasted directly into MS Word, Google Docs, or Vellum:

# [Book Title / Part Title] ──> Standard H1 (MS Word Title Style)
## [Chapter Title] ──> Standard H2 (MS Word Heading 1)
### [Subchapter Title] ──> Standard H3 (MS Word Heading 2)

**[Text]** ──> Strict Bold (For key realizations, contrasting clashes, and structural emphasis)
*[Text]* ──> Strict Italics (For Scout's internal thoughts, parenthetical whispers, and conversational footnote text)

Whitespace Rules:
Double line breaks between paragraphs to prevent screen-merging on Kindle and ensure elegant block-paragraph pacing when pasted.